Important Anniversaries in DPRK Observed in Foreign Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- Seminars on the Songun politics were held by the Dar-Es-Salaam Provincial Committee of the Revolutionary Party of Tanzania and the British Association for the Study of the Songun Policy and a seminar on the subject of "Let us achieve victory of socialism for humankind" by the Lebanese Youth Group for the Study of the Juche Idea from July 30 to August 1 on the occasion of the 52nd anniversary of the victory in the great Fatherland Liberation War and the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea. 
 The deputy secretary of the Dar-Es-Salaam Provincial Committee of the Tanzanian party in a speech said that the DPRK is pursuing independent politics without reading others' faces and standing firm against the United States styling itself "the world's only superpower," adding that this is thanks to the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il who has trained the Korean People's Army into an invincible army and glorified Korean-style socialism with the Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to this politics of Kim Jong Il the Korean people will build a great prosperous powerful nation in the near future, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the British association in his report explained how the Songun politics was set out and its great validity and vitality and how it is being successfully pursued in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the Lebanese group and other figures in their report and speeches praised President Kim Il Sung as a great leader who trained the Korean people into a great and heroic people and  Kim Jong Il as the sun of the 21st century as he has turned the DPRK into an invulnerable fortress on the anti-imperialist front and is building it into a great prosperous powerful socialist nation.

Japanese reactionaries' Negation of Past History under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- We denounce the Japanese reactionaries for undisguisedly revealing their militarist ambition for staging a comeback to Korea, totally negating Japan's blood-stained history of aggression against Korea.
 A spokesman for the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea said this in a statement issued on August 10 in the run-up to the 60th anniversary of the Japanese imperialists' defeat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the Korean people and progressive humankind are strongly demanding Japan apologize and repent of its past crimes and compensate for them, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are getting more frantic in their anti-DPRK racket, negating and distorting Japan's history of aggression in the past and raising a hue and cry over the "nuclear issue" and "abduction issue" in a bid to divert elsewhere the attention of the unbiased world public demanding the liquidation of its past crimes and evade its responsibility for them even after the adoption of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The agricultural workers' hatred and resentment against the Japanese reactionaries are running high as they are desperately pursuing a hostile policy toward the DPRK, persistently refusing to make apology and compensation for the unspeakable sufferings and pain imposed by them upon the Korean people after invading Korea in the past.
 If the Japanese reactionaries continue resorting to a clumsy trick to evade the responsibility for the past crimes while refusing to apologize and compensate for them, the agricultural workers will surely force them to pay for all crimes with the determination to take a thousand-fold revenge upon them.

Collection of Kim Jong Il's Works Published 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- "For the National Reunification and the Great National Unity", a collection of leader Kim Jong Il's works, was brought out by the Workers' Party of Korea Publishing House.
 Contained in the collection are 16 celebrated works on the problem of national reunification, including treatises, letters and talks, he published in the period from July, Juche 61 (1972), to June, Juche 89 (2000). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In "Let Us Resolutely Struggle to Implement the Three Principles of National Reunification" and other works  Kim Jong Il noted that the north and the south agreed upon the three principles of national reunification and promised the whole nation and the world to implement them, thus making it possible for the Korean people to invigorate the movement for national reunification with the clear principles and standard. And he stressed the need to hold fast to the three principles and wage a dynamic struggle in reliance on them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are works "The National Reunification Should Be Achieved by the Great Unity of the Nation" and "The Reunification of the Country Should Be Achieved Independently by the Concerted Efforts of Our Nation", which carry the ideas and theories on reunifying the country with great unity of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In his work "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Comrade  Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification" Kim Jong Il said that the three principles of national reunification, the ten-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding a Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo are the three charters for national reunification advanced by President Kim Il Sung. Basing himself on them,   Kim Jong Il clarified the tasks and ways for realizing the cause of national reunification, the supreme desire of the nation.

Japan Defense Agency's "National Defense White Paper" Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- The Japan Defense Agency in its "national defense white paper" for 2005 published recently groundlessly pulled up and attacked the DPRK, terming it "a major factor of instability" in Northeast Asia. In this regard Rodong Sinmun Thursday observes in a signed commentary: The claim made by the Japan Defense Agency is nothing but sophism making a profound confusion of right and wrong and part of a vicious smear campaign against the DPRK.
 The ultra right forces of Japan have launched a campaign for visits of 200,000 people to the "Yasukuni Shrine" on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the defeat of the Japanese imperialists while the LDP committee for drafting a new constitution formally made public a "draft amendment to the constitution" aimed at legislating on the possession of regular armed forces and militarizing the Japanese society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What remains to be done now is just to get a chance for launching military reinvasion. It is in pursuance of this aim that the Japanese warlike forces are painting the DPRK as a "major factor of instability" under the absurd pretext of "military threat" from it.
 Japan predicts that its moves to grab others' territories for its territorial expansion may spark regional disputes and, furthermore, lead to armed conflicts to bring irrevocable serious consequences to Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the height of crafty and shameless nature of Japan to term the DPRK "factor of instability" though the former is chiefly to blame for threatening peace and stability in the region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan would be well advised to bear in mind that the reinvasion to be launched by it at any cost, seized by its inveterate bad habit, would only entail disastrous consequences.

Fuller Play to Might of Songun Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- The joint slogans of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea fully reflect the unshakable faith and will of the Party to accomplish the cause of Korean-style socialism by force of Songun without fail which has been defended and glorified by Songun.
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a by-lined article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To give fuller play to the might of Songun provides a sure guarantee for a victory in the on-going general march as the validity and vitality of Songun have been clearly proven in the stern test of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans reflect the revolutionary will of the Party and the people to demonstrate the mettle of Juche Korea to the world under the uplifted banner of Songun and the steadfast revolutionary stand of the Party to bring a decisive turning point in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation by the force of single-minded unity, the mainstay of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is prerequisite for exalting the dignity and honor of the country by the force of Songun for the army and people to thoroughly arm themselves with the Songun idea of leader Kim Jong Il and eternally glorify his Songun leadership feats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Songun is the only way of smashing the vicious moves of the U.S. imperialists to bring down the socialist system in Korea and win a decisive victory in the showdown with the U.S. Only when the might of Songun is given full play, can a new turning point be brought about in the socialist economic construction aimed to reach the high eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It is necessary to hold higher the banner of Songun in order to arm all members of the society with the revolutionary soldier spirit of the Korean People's Army, the pioneer and standard- bearer in the era of Songun, and make the revolutionary and militant lifestyle and revolutionary soldier culture of the People's Army prevail throughout the society.

More Summer Birds Come to DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- This summer a larger number of migratory birds have come to the Democratic People's Republic of Korea than usual.
 Seen in the country are more than 110 kinds of summer birds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them over 20 kinds of birds including Horeites cantans, Acrocephalus ardinaces, Motacilla flava and Emberiza tristrami Swinh have sharply increased in number this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the number of Halcyon coromanda, Halcyon pileata, Phylloscopus tonelipes Swinh, Emberiza spodocephala Pall and others nearly doubles that in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Scarlet-finch, needle-tailed swift and various other species of seasonal birds, their number being 1.5 times that of the last year, have flown into the dense forest around the secret camp in Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, an increasing number of birds belonging to Egretta and Rallidae have nestled in west coastal areas of the country and Saxicola torguata Steju in the central area. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government has set March and July every year as the period for protecting useful animals and organized various activities such as tree-planting, river and swampy land improvement and installation of artificial nests to provide good environment to birds.
 A special attention has been directed to making favorable conditions for the protection and propagation of birds.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from Foreigners
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il Thursday received a letter from the participants in the Meeting Dedicated to the Great Persons of Mt. Paektu.
 The letter noted that Mt. Paektu is well-known to the world as it is associated with the precious feats of the great persons of Mt. Paektu who made particular contributions to the human cause of independence and the movement for national liberation and, especially, it is a sacred place where the great Songun revolutionary leadership was started. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that it is the beautiful nature of human being to follow and revere a great man, the letter said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 You have further fortified socialist Korea as an invincible bulwark of Songun to defend justice in the present intricate world where high-handedness and arbitrariness of the imperialists are rampant, instilling hope and confidence into the revolutionary people aspiring after independence. So, it is quite natural for the progressive humankind to highly praise and follow you as a veteran statesman of the world and the sun of the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Currently going round the Mt. Paektu area, including your old home in the sacred camp of the mountain, with deep emotion, we came to know well about the source of the might of the heroic Korean people who are dynamically advancing under the banner of Songun along the road of the revolutionary cause of Juche started on Mt. Paektu.
 We will more vigorously conduct the activities of introducing the greatness and Songun feats of the three generals of Mt. Paektu and the solidarity movement for supporting the just cause of the Korean people led by you, true to the resolution we made before the world on sacred Mt. Paektu today.
